                            <comment id="17034344" author="jark" created="Tue, 11 Feb 2020 11:09:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we can just remove the &lt;tt&gt;this.getClass().getClassLoader()&lt;/tt&gt; parameter, the underlying of TableFactoryService will use thread context classloader as default. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Btw, if the flink-connector-kafka is placed in flink-dist/lib/, then the BootStrapClassLoader should find the class. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17034349" author="victor-wong" created="Tue, 11 Feb 2020 11:15:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s right, we can just remove the this.getClass().getClassLoader() parameter.&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/thumbs_up.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As the second question, the required TableFactory was configured in the user jar, so the BootStrapClassLoader could not find the class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
